<br>
 I want to continue my dual-wielding, but in a forum...somewhere... I saw where a blademaster specced high in Weapon, Parry, then low 40s for shield. He then brought up CD to the mid-20s...<br>
<br>
 His point was... He would use the dual weapons, but have the shield readied in the over-hand/back slot. He would click on it, bash the enemy, effectively stunning it, and bring out his other sword again to continue bashing on him.<br>
<br>
My question(s) is this:  Is it worth it?  <br>
                                Does it work?<br>
                                Should i respec my points into it?<br>
                                Is the sacrifice in the other areas truly going to make that big of a difference? (since we are so terribly gimped in our damage output)<br>
<br>
Thanks for the input! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=craess>craess</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://media.ign.com/boards/images/icons/matrix_pills.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#000000>(3/11/03 9:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=90.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dual wield...with shield spec?</span><hr size=1> it doesn't really work very well since the off ahnd and shield use the same slot... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cervanntes>cervanntes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#000000>(5/1/03 9:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=90.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dual wield...with shield spec?</span><hr size=1> I took a slightly different route.  I'm Celtic Dual primarily, with a healthy dose of parry and blades.  I did put some points into shield, however, for one primary reason - to assist myself and others during a seige.  Quite often, there comes a point where hand-to-hand slows and it falls to primarily missile and magic fire during a keep take.  At this point, having two weapons in hand becomes rather pointless, unless you just plan on prowling for the inevitable stealthers and suicide tanks.  I find I far prefer using a shield at this stage in a seige, covering a healer if necessary and myself in any case as we work on the doors.  For that reason and that reason alone, I made a very early investment in Shield specc, if only to get the Guard ability.  Yes, the odds of blocking arrows are slim at such a low specc, but slim is better than no chance at all, and that second weapon seldom does me any good when in that particular stage of a seige.  In the worst case scenario, I can use Numb (3 spec shield, anytime low stun) to stall an attacker long enough to switch to my second weapon, so I've lost nothing...and I really don't need the Numb.  Swapping weapon and shield in the off-hand is fairly simple if you practice it a bit. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fingoniel>Fingoniel</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://forums.barrysworld.com/avatar.php?userid=16042&dateline=1026917502" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Determined Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 258<br> <font color=#000000>(5/2/03 5:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=90.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dual wield...with shield spec?</span><hr size=1> I'm a merc so slightly different <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  but I specced 50 dual 42 slash 32 parry 23 shield<br>
<br>
23 shield gives you a 6s rear stun.<br>
<br>
Now I'm under no delusions that I can switch mid-slam (well, paralyze)  but I can choose to play defensively or offensively at the start of the fight, and flip to dual wielding when I run out of end (or keep the shield for blocking)<br>
<br>
If I'm the only shield tank in the group I'll play defensive - paralyzing and preventing flight on the enemy tanks...<br>
Or if I feel like doing some damage I just keep my two swords and go chop up some casters/healers <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Fingoniel MacAlpine<br>
