<br>
My spec is :<br>
<br>
41-pierce (57)<br>
42-shield (5<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
39-CD (55)<br>
29-parry (45)<br>
<br>
(+16 to each)<br>
<br>
It's not nearly as difficult as some think to swpa shield/offhand out.  Yes, you have to do it manually, but the versatility to be able to slam anyone at any time, then taking approximately 1-2secs (lag sucks) to switch out and deal as much dmg to them while they're vulnerable, is worth it imo.  Yes, slam eats endurance up, but there are ways around that as well.  Using a reinforced small shield rather then a medium will reduce end cost.  Once your target is stunned, strafe to the side and position yourself WHILE your switching out, and perform high dmg, low end cost styles.  It evens out endurance wise, and takes your target out of combat long enough to dispatch.<br>
<br>
You don't have to continually switch out either.  With the lack of shield spec guardians in RvR, you'll be welcome into any group to guard cloth/support classes.  I recall one time while with a bard and enchanter in Emain and taking out a 5-6 man alb group.  Unfortunately, they all stuck the enchanter, whom I was guarding, and effectively blocked 60+% of the attacks towards him while he mocc'ed <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
It's a diverse spec that has more utility in my opinion, but I won;t say it's better then any other template.  It's all dependant on how YOU want to play, and which role/roles you excell at.  (I'm just fond of taking on more then one role <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
